I feel like he's watching us.

07:45.040 --> 07:47.646
No, he's not my friend.

07:49.880 --> 07:51.580
He's my bodyguard.

07:51.680 --> 07:53.380
Come on.

07:53.480 --> 07:56.260
Something like that.

07:56.360 --> 07:59.260
It's a funny word, isn't it, bodyguard?

07:59.360 --> 08:01.044
- Uh...
- Bodyguard.

08:03.280 --> 08:05.760
- Are we on "Candid Camera"?
- No.

08:05.880 --> 08:09.487
No, no, no. I do need a car.

08:14.160 --> 08:15.571
Can we just sit in here for a minute?

08:17.080 --> 08:18.730
Sure.

08:28.520 --> 08:30.300
Well, the master lock feature works.

08:30.400 --> 08:31.900
We know that much.

08:32.000 --> 08:33.604
Hmm.

08:42.480 --> 08:44.482
My brother died.

08:46.240 --> 08:48.527
Oh. Oh, I'm...

08:49.720 --> 08:51.165
I'm so sorry.

08:54.600 --> 08:57.020
He drowned.

08:57.120 --> 08:59.060
A few years ago.

08:59.160 --> 09:00.764
Two.

09:02.680 --> 09:05.940
But I'm all...
broken up about it still, you know?

09:06.040 --> 09:08.486
I mean, he wasn't even 40 yet.

09:09.560 --> 09:12.060
That is... that's terrible.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.860
- So sad.
- Yeah.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.340
But I just don't get it.

09:16.440 --> 09:19.660
I think about it every day,
and I just don't get it.

09:19.760 --> 09:21.580
I guess it's better just
not to think about it, right?

09:21.680 --> 09:23.180
Just...

09:23.280 --> 09:25.220
force it out of your mind.

09:25.320 --> 09:28.688
Sure. Yeah, I can understand that.

09:36.240 --> 09:38.129
I'm not married anymore.

09:43.520 --> 09:45.329
Okay.

09:48.560 --> 09:50.722
Do you have a pen I could use?

10:00.600 --> 10:03.060
I guess I need
a little piece of paper, too.

10:03.160 --> 10:05.020
Uh, sure. Just, um...

10:05.120 --> 10:06.610
Thank you.

10:12.880 --> 10:14.848
Brian, come on out of the car.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.570
- I'm Brian.
- Melinda.

10:19.680 --> 10:20.329
- Hi.
- Hi.

10:20.440 --> 10:22.300
- Come on, Brian.
- I want this car.

10:22.400 --> 10:23.980
-
- The Fleetwood?

10:24.080 --> 10:26.287
No, no, yeah, but I want this car. Okay?

10:28.280 --> 10:30.940
I want this car.
This one we're sitting in.

10:31.040 --> 10:34.660
- Oh, the floor model?
- Yes, it's your favorite, right?

10:34.760 --> 10:37.740
- You want...
- It's special. You understand?

10:37.840 --> 10:39.700
- Can I have it?
- Sure.

10:39.800 --> 10:41.723
- Okay.
- Yes.

10:45.080 --> 10:46.500
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:46.600 --> 10:47.886
- What's happening, guys?
- Hi, Gene.

10:48.000 --> 10:50.980
- Hi, I'm Dr. Eugene Landy.
- Hi.

10:51.080 --> 10:53.020
How are you?

10:53.120 --> 10:55.860
I'm Brian's brother from another mother.

10:55.960 --> 10:57.940
- What's up?
- I want the blue Fleetwood, Gene.

10:58.040 --> 11:00.380
- Really?
- Yeah.

11:00.480 --> 11:02.780
You sure you don't want a Maserati?

11:02.880 --> 11:04.860
- No offense.
- None taken.

11:04.960 --> 11:06.860
- No, that one.
- Really?

11:06.960 --> 11:09.220
- It's her favorite.
- Okay.

11:09.320 --> 11:12.900
Well, I'm going to expect
a deal here. You know?

11:13.000 --> 11:14.380
Something worth our while.

11:14.480 --> 11:17.051
Do you know who this man is?
Brian Wilson.

11:18.640 --> 11:21.530
Brian Wilson of the Beach Boys.

11:25.320 --> 11:28.340
- You didn't mention that.
- Well, 'cause that stuff doesn't matter.

11:28.440 --> 11:29.980
That's ego stuff. You know?

11:30.080 --> 11:31.900
Are you kidding me?

11:32.000 --> 11:33.660
I love your music. I grew up on it.

11:33.760 --> 11:35.220
So, thank you.

11:35.320 --> 11:37.620
That makes me feel really good,
Melinda Ledbetter.

11:37.720 --> 11:40.300
Okay.

11:40.400 --> 11:42.860
- Melinda Ledbetter.
- Right? It's a nice name.

11:42.960 --> 11:45.220
Uh, why don't you get started
on the paperwork?

11:45.320 --> 11:47.580
- Okay?
- Will do.

11:47.680 --> 11:50.100
Great. And thank you again
for your help.

11:50.200 --> 11:51.645
Let's go, Brian.

11:52.920 --> 11:54.540
Come on, guy.

11:54.640 --> 11:55.900
I think it's a good choice.

11:56.000 --> 11:57.240
- You feel good about it?
- Yeah.

11:57.360 --> 11:58.620
- You sure?
- Yeah.

11:58.720 --> 11:59.960
Okay.

12:03.480 --> 12:05.642
What the hell was that about?

12:07.880 --> 12:09.803
I'm not really sure.

12:11.400 --> 12:13.050
You okay?

12:14.960 --> 12:18.248
Yeah.

12:38.400 --> 12:41.460
Ladies and gentlemen,
we're about to start our descent.

12:41.560 --> 12:43.580
Please return your seats
to an upright position...

12:43.680 --> 12:45.489
and fasten your seat belts.

12:57.400 --> 12:59.880
You okay?

13:02.000 --> 13:03.445
I think I'm having a heart attack.

13:20.120 --> 13:21.485
Brian! Brian!

13:23.640 --> 13:25.180
- Brian! Brian! Brian!
- Get him something!

13:25.280 --> 13:26.500
- Bring us a pillow!
- Breathe!

13:26.600 --> 13:27.860
- Give me the pillow!
- Where's the pillow?!

13:27.960 --> 13:30.042
Give me the pillow!

13:30.160 --> 13:31.220
- Brian! Brian!
- Breathe!

13:31.320 --> 13:32.820
Are you choking? Are you choking?

13:32.920 --> 13:34.500
- I don't want to die!
- Hey!

13:34.600 --> 13:36.060
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
- I don't want to die!

13:36.160 --> 13:38.540
Brian, look at me.
Look at me! Look at me!

13:38.640 --> 13:40.580
Look at me! Look at me. Look at me.

13:40.680 --> 13:42.250
It's okay.

13:44.320 --> 13:45.940
Hi.

13:46.040 --> 13:47.849
You good?

13:48.920 --> 13:51.740
Nowhere to run to, baby.

13:51.840 --> 13:53.100
It was weird.

13:53.200 --> 13:54.780
It was like I was in a movie
or something.

13:54.880 --> 13:57.100
There was music, like always...

13:57.200 --> 13:59.580
but then it got dark and scary.

13:59.680 --> 14:01.860
I couldn't breathe.

14:01.960 --> 14:03.860
Like someone was holding
his hand over my mouth.

14:03.960 --> 14:06.620
Hey, Brian. You doing okay, baby?

14:06.720 --> 14:08.860
Yeah, I'm good, Mare.

14:08.960 --> 14:11.361
Okay, just checking.

14:12.960 --> 14:14.740
Yeah, then I started hearing things.

14:14.840 --> 14:16.580
Strange things.

14:16.680 --> 14:19.300
- People talking.
- What, like voices?

14:19.400 --> 14:21.620
Like, uh...

14:21.720 --> 14:23.540
like voices in your head?

14:23.640 --> 14:25.130
No!

14:26.600 --> 14:30.180
Well, kind of. Yeah.

14:30.280 --> 14:33.020
Maybe I'm cuckoo for Cocoa Puffs!

14:33.120 --> 14:34.451
Cuckoo for Cocoa Puffs!

14:34.560 --> 14:36.020
It was kind of scary.

14:36.120 --> 14:39.580
I think it's just Dad. You know?
Messing with your head.

14:39.680 --> 14:41.900
We're too big for him
to take the belt to us anymore...

14:42.000 --> 14:45.020
so he's got to use
his black magic shit or something.

14:45.120 --> 14:46.420
Ah, come on. It's not Dad.

14:46.520 --> 14:48.380
- Yeah...
- Something's off.

14:48.480 --> 14:50.500
It's being on the road.

14:50.600 --> 14:52.380
You know, being up there. It's freaky.

14:52.480 --> 14:53.900
I get nervous onstage, too, Bri.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.700
- I mean, we all probably do.
- No, but this is different.

14:56.800 --> 14:59.620
Anyway, you don't need me
standing up there...

14:59.720 --> 15:01.940
looking like a jerk.

15:02.040 --> 15:04.100
I'll be better back here at home.

15:04.200 --> 15:05.860
Making music.

15:05.960 --> 15:07.980
I just want to be home.

15:08.080 --> 15:10.380
I got all kinds of new ideas...

15:10.480 --> 15:12.060
new sounds...

15:12.160 --> 15:13.780
new harmonies...

15:13.880 --> 15:16.060
new instruments.

15:16.160 --> 15:17.446
You hear the new Beatles?

15:17.560 --> 15:19.660
- Yeah.
- The "Rubber Soul"? Yeah.

15:19.760 --> 15:22.420
I heard it was about
John Lennon having an affair.

15:22.520 --> 15:23.860
It's amazing!

15:23.960 --> 15:25.700
I mean, it works like a whole.

15:25.800 --> 15:28.020
It's like a whole album.

15:28.120 --> 15:29.940
Everything fits together, no fat.

15:30.040 --> 15:32.940
Like an album of folk songs,
but the sounds are really far out.

15:33.040 --> 15:35.220
- Lots of overdubbing.
- They stole our backing vocal.

15:35.320 --> 15:37.971
You know, we go,
La, la, la, la, la, la...

15:38.080 --> 15:39.700
And then they changed it to...

15:39.800 --> 15:42.140
De, de, de, de, de, de, de, de, de...

15:42.240 --> 15:45.820
I thought it said,
"Tit, tit, tit, tits, titties."

15:45.920 --> 15:47.300
- No?
- Denny.

15:47.400 --> 15:49.340
We can't let them get ahead of us!

15:49.440 --> 15:50.540
J...

15:50.640 --> 15:52.420
I can take us further.

15:52.520 --> 15:55.980
If you let me
stay at home in the studio.

15:56.080 --> 15:58.481
It's what I need to do.

15:58.600 --> 16:00.620
And I promise, when you come back...

16:00.720 --> 16:04.406
I will have stuff for you
that will blow your minds.

16:07.200 --> 16:08.247
Bri!

16:08.360 --> 16:10.169
Fine, but you just keep
your head on straight.

16:10.280 --> 16:11.340
- Okay, Bri?
- I will!

16:11.440 --> 16:13.340
- Hey, Brian!
- I will.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.820
Straight as a die.

16:15.920 --> 16:17.580
Hey, straight as a what?

16:17.680 --> 16:18.820
What does that even mean?

16:18.920 --> 16:20.020
You're going to die in a straight line?

16:20.120 --> 16:21.780
I have no idea. I heard Dad use it once.

16:21.880 --> 16:24.660
Oh, never use it again.

16:24.760 --> 16:27.540
It's going to be strange
to be in Japan without you, brother.

16:27.640 --> 16:30.380
Yeah, who's going to fold
our clothes now?

16:30.480 --> 16:32.540
Bri!

16:32.640 --> 16:34.780
Carl, Dennis, come on,
guys, come sit with us.

16:34.880 --> 16:37.486
Okay, I'll be right over.

16:42.280 --> 16:44.442
Everybody in!

16:48.560 --> 16:50.340
One of these days,
you are going to break...

16:50.440 --> 16:53.340
your skull open
if you're not careful, Bri.

16:53.440 --> 16:55.860
I'm going to make the greatest album
ever made, Mare!

16:55.960 --> 16:57.860
I know you are, baby.

16:57.960 --> 16:59.660
I know you are.

16:59.760 --> 17:02.340
Ben, two more minutes, I'm almost ready.

17:02.440 --> 17:03.646
You can lock up.

