Thoughts they cannot defend...

19:26.600 --> 19:31.288
Just what you want to be...

19:39.480 --> 19:41.403
Well...

19:43.080 --> 19:45.128
I guess this is good night.

19:50.120 --> 19:51.531
Good night.

19:53.720 --> 19:56.326
- Okay.
- Would you like me to call you again?

19:59.560 --> 20:01.340
Would you like to call me again?

20:01.440 --> 20:04.808
Or... are you just asking
'cause you were told to?

20:07.040 --> 20:09.202
Both things.

20:11.640 --> 20:14.700
- Both.
- I really appreciate your honesty.

20:14.800 --> 20:17.849
I really do. I don't meet
a lot of honest people anymore.

20:19.680 --> 20:20.780
I'll tell you what.

20:20.880 --> 20:24.043
I'm going to be home
most of the day Sunday.

20:24.160 --> 20:25.860
Give me a call if you feel like it.

20:25.960 --> 20:28.180
If you don't, that's fine, too.
There's no pressure.

20:28.280 --> 20:29.691
I'm going to call you.

20:31.440 --> 20:33.169
- Cool.
- Cool.

20:39.360 --> 20:40.805
Good night.

20:42.960 --> 20:44.291
Good night.

21:06.680 --> 21:10.571
I may not always love you...

21:12.320 --> 21:17.008
but long as there are stars above you...

21:18.680 --> 21:23.049
you never need to doubt it.

21:24.240 --> 21:29.041
I'll make you so sure about it.

21:30.400 --> 21:32.140
And God only knows...

21:32.240 --> 21:35.961
what I'd be without you.

21:40.840 --> 21:45.980
If you should ever leave me...

21:46.080 --> 21:51.300
well, life would still go on,
believe me.

21:51.400 --> 21:56.340
The world could show nothing to me...

21:56.440 --> 22:01.731
so what good would living do me?...

22:01.840 --> 22:03.683
And God only knows...

22:03.800 --> 22:07.407
what I'd be without you.

22:11.960 --> 22:13.700
And God only knows...

22:13.800 --> 22:18.442
what I'd be without you.

22:22.400 --> 22:24.380
And the last verse
repeats one more time...

22:24.480 --> 22:27.006
and the chorus will harmonize
over and over at the end.

22:28.600 --> 22:30.740
It's still rough, I know,
but it's getting there.

22:30.840 --> 22:32.900
It's right for Carl's voice.

22:33.000 --> 22:34.820
You like it, Dad?

22:34.920 --> 22:37.100
I mean, it'll get better.
The vocals will...

22:37.200 --> 22:39.540
counterpoint the backing track.

22:39.640 --> 22:41.165
Real soulful.

22:43.480 --> 22:46.609
Oh, you don't want
my advice or my meddling.

22:48.080 --> 22:50.060
Well, just tell me what you think.

22:50.160 --> 22:52.580
Not much use for me, is there?

22:52.680 --> 22:54.260
With your mom living on her own.

22:54.360 --> 22:57.011
Come on, we're still a family.

22:58.320 --> 23:01.780
Families don't fire their own father.

23:01.880 --> 23:03.660
I don't want to start
that argument again.

23:03.760 --> 23:06.820
- I'm not arguing.
- If I say something now, you'll argue.

23:06.920 --> 23:08.763
Then don't say anything.

23:09.760 --> 23:11.260
Forget it!

23:11.360 --> 23:13.860
Forget what? Forget what?

23:13.960 --> 23:16.420
- You don't like the song.
- I never said that.

23:16.520 --> 23:19.126
I can tell.

23:20.520 --> 23:22.300
Just say something!

23:22.400 --> 23:24.420
I would change the title.

23:24.520 --> 23:27.460
The Capris had a tune out
called "God Only Knows"...

23:27.560 --> 23:30.980
- in '55, '54.
- Never mind that.

23:31.080 --> 23:33.100
Did you close your eyes
like I asked you to?

23:33.200 --> 23:35.260
Tony and I think...

23:35.360 --> 23:38.409
if you close your eyes,
you can see a place...

23:38.520 --> 23:41.100
where something is happening.

23:41.200 --> 23:43.660
It's like being blind, but because
you're blind, you can see more.

23:43.760 --> 23:45.780
Don't you think
it's a spiritual kind of thing?

23:45.880 --> 23:49.168
I don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

23:49.280 --> 23:52.124
I closed my eyes, didn't see a thing.

23:54.120 --> 23:56.740
I don't know,
maybe it could be something...

23:56.840 --> 23:58.500
with the right arrangement.

23:58.600 --> 24:00.260
Well, yeah, I have French horns on it...

24:00.360 --> 24:03.060
and flutes, tambourines,
sleigh bells, piano, bass...

24:03.160 --> 24:05.003
real complex key shifts.

24:07.120 --> 24:08.780
Frankly, if you really want to know...

24:08.880 --> 24:10.540
I don't care for it.

24:10.640 --> 24:12.220
It's too wishy-washy.

24:12.320 --> 24:14.820
If you leave me, why leave me?

24:14.920 --> 24:17.820
Life will go on, why go on living?

24:17.920 --> 24:19.540
It's not like a Beach Boys song.

24:19.640 --> 24:21.369
Your brothers are going to hate it.

24:21.480 --> 24:24.820
- It's a love song.
- It's a suicide note.

24:24.920 --> 24:27.180
Didn't you just say it could be something
with the right arrangement?!

24:27.280 --> 24:30.740
Well, I gave it another thought, okay?

24:30.840 --> 24:32.660
And if you can't keep
your voice down in my house...

24:32.760 --> 24:34.091
get out!

24:53.720 --> 24:55.180
Hey, Carol.

24:55.280 --> 24:57.380
- How's it going?
- Good. Good to see you.

24:57.480 --> 24:58.860
Groovy shades.

24:58.960 --> 25:00.689
Lyle, how's it going?

25:03.040 --> 25:05.460
- Hal, hey. Good to see you.
- Hey. You, too.

25:05.560 --> 25:06.780
I want you to meet Tony Asher.

25:06.880 --> 25:08.140
Tony Asher, this is Hal Blaine.

25:08.240 --> 25:10.300
The greatest drummer working today.

25:10.400 --> 25:11.860
And you never heard of him, have you?

25:11.960 --> 25:13.166
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

25:13.280 --> 25:16.300
That's the secret.
All these guys, Hal, Tommy, Carol, Earl...

25:16.400 --> 25:18.420
the whole band.
I mean, they're probably...

25:18.520 --> 25:21.420
the best in the business,
but they're studio musicians...

25:21.520 --> 25:23.700
so nobody's ever heard of them.
It's crazy!

25:23.800 --> 25:25.340
- Huh?
- Yeah, oh, yeah.

25:25.440 --> 25:27.329
Yeah. Here you go.

25:28.680 --> 25:31.286
Kettle drums?
Thought we were doing rock 'n' roll.

25:33.200 --> 25:35.340
Ah, a whole new bag.

25:35.440 --> 25:37.420
So what do we got going here, Brian?

25:37.520 --> 25:40.620
Uh, I don't know, Hal. Just some ideas.

25:40.720 --> 25:42.580
Try something.

25:42.680 --> 25:44.250
Oh, excuse me.

25:48.280 --> 25:50.860
- Bum, bum, bum.
- Yup.

25:50.960 --> 25:52.086
Yeah, let's try it.

25:54.440 --> 25:55.680
Mmm.

26:01.480 --> 26:03.528
That's exactly how I want it.

26:04.680 --> 26:05.841
You know what I'm going to do?

26:05.960 --> 26:07.260
Let's add a little tie right here.

26:07.360 --> 26:08.805
I think this will sound better...

26:08.920 --> 26:12.420
- a little smoother right there.
- You want to tie the first one?

26:12.520 --> 26:15.100
Okay, this is "I'm Waiting
For the Day," take six.

26:15.200 --> 26:18.921
Here we go. One, two, one, two, three.

26:43.400 --> 26:45.460
Oh, hey! That was out of sight.

26:45.560 --> 26:47.980
I mean, it really was, Al.
How did you play that?

26:48.080 --> 26:50.500
- I don't know.
- What?

26:50.600 --> 26:52.125
The, uh...

26:52.760 --> 26:54.125
How did you play that?

26:56.040 --> 26:58.500
- It was a mistake.
- Well, if you repeat a mistake...

26:58.600 --> 27:00.740
every four bars,
it's not a mistake anymore.

27:00.840 --> 27:02.460
- See what I mean?
- I love it.

27:02.560 --> 27:03.482
All right.

27:04.920 --> 27:06.968
That was great. Okay, let's do it again.

27:39.600 --> 27:43.260
Remember, it's the higher octave
on the upbeats and the bridge.

27:43.360 --> 27:45.580
Hey, Brian?

27:45.680 --> 27:47.020
- Yeah, I love that.
- Brian?

27:47.120 --> 27:49.700
- Yeah?
- I think you might've screwed up here.

27:49.800 --> 27:51.100
Really? Let me see.

27:51.200 --> 27:53.100
Well, you've got Lyle playing in D...

27:53.200 --> 27:56.060
- and the rest of us are in A major.
- Yeah, that's right.

27:56.160 --> 27:59.380
How does that work?
Two bass lines in two different keys?

27:59.480 --> 28:01.540
Well, it works in my head.

28:01.640 --> 28:02.860
It's all playing in my head.

28:02.960 --> 28:04.928
The orchestration
and the five vocal parts.

28:06.680 --> 28:08.420
I think it's going to work.
Let's try it.

28:08.520 --> 28:10.780
Oh, Hal? Hal?

28:10.880 --> 28:12.769
Here's how I want you
to do it. It goes, uh...

28:19.120 --> 28:20.300
Two, three, four.

28:20.400 --> 28:22.540
So it's, uh...

28:22.640 --> 28:24.420
the first beat
on the last bar of the intro.

28:24.520 --> 28:26.522
Boom! Two, three, four.

28:39.120 --> 28:40.580
There's the North Star right there.

28:40.680 --> 28:43.740
- That's the North Star?
- Yeah, yeah. You knew that.

28:43.840 --> 28:47.100
- I really didn't.
- Come on.

28:47.200 --> 28:49.060
- I mean, it's a bright star.
- Have you ever...

28:49.160 --> 28:50.460
have you ever seen this before?

28:50.560 --> 28:52.289
- Never like this.
- Yeah.

28:53.560 --> 28:55.900
I used to love
coming here as a kid, you know?

28:56.000 --> 28:58.260
I love the feel of this place.

28:58.360 --> 29:00.140
I really wanted to take you here.

29:00.240 --> 29:02.083
- You did?
- Yeah.

29:10.160 --> 29:13.180
Demonstration booths.
Do you remember those?

29:13.280 --> 29:16.284
- In the department store?
- Yeah, and that's when I first heard...

29:16.400 --> 29:18.140
The Four Freshmen...

29:18.240 --> 29:21.005
and immediately my mind just...

29:22.200 --> 29:23.660
I mean, it's... like magic.

29:23.760 --> 29:25.420
Something happened and...

29:25.520 --> 29:28.620
so I listened to those harmonies
and study them after school,

29:28.720 --> 29:31.380
and I would teach them to my brothers.

29:31.480 --> 29:33.140
And we'd all sing.

29:33.240 --> 29:34.700
And then I would teach them
to my parents...

29:34.800 --> 29:36.060
and we'd all be sitting around singing.

29:36.160 --> 29:38.811
My brothers and my parents
and everybody.

29:38.920 --> 29:39.980
Everybody.

29:40.080 --> 29:42.940
Wow. That sounds like
such a wonderful childhood.

29:43.040 --> 29:44.644
Yeah, it was really nice...

29:44.760 --> 29:46.980
except for when my dad
was beating on us...

29:47.080 --> 29:49.180
all the time, you know? Like...

29:49.280 --> 29:53.140
He was a really hard, hard guy.

29:53.240 --> 29:55.049
You know, like, um...

29:56.760 --> 29:59.780
There's a spanking. You know that sound?

29:59.880 --> 30:01.380
You know a certain kind of spanking...

30:01.480 --> 30:03.084
and it sounds like a...
you know, like...

30:05.440 --> 30:07.260
But the way we had it, you know?

30:07.360 --> 30:09.820
When it came out of him, it's...

30:09.920 --> 30:13.380
You know?

30:13.480 --> 30:14.925
Really hard.

30:15.040 --> 30:17.340
Come on, let's give
these guys some privacy.

30:17.440 --> 30:19.060
- You know, we laugh about it.
- Babe, I can't just...

30:19.160 --> 30:20.900
- Doug, come on.
- You know, back in those days?

30:21.000 --> 30:23.180
We laugh about all that, but...

30:23.280 --> 30:26.329
it was pretty tough business.

30:27.320 --> 30:28.731
Pretty tough business.

30:30.640 --> 30:32.220
Hey.

30:32.320 --> 30:35.020
- I'm so sorry.
- No, what? About what?

30:35.120 --> 30:37.180
They're okay.
They come here all the time.

30:37.280 --> 30:40.740
- It's their favorite spot.
- No, Brian, about your dad.

30:40.840 --> 30:42.808
Oh, yeah.

30:43.800 --> 30:45.540
You know, spare... spare the rod...

30:45.640 --> 30:47.324
spoil the child.

30:48.640 --> 30:50.700
You know I'm 96% deaf...

30:50.800 --> 30:53.963
in my right ear because
my dad whacked me all the time?

30:54.960 --> 30:56.820
He was a really hard man...

30:56.920 --> 30:59.020
and he was a not very happy man...

30:59.120 --> 31:01.100
but, uh...

31:01.200 --> 31:03.500
in some ways I love my dad,
you know, because...

31:03.600 --> 31:05.220
he scared me and he scared me so much...

31:05.320 --> 31:07.740
I think he actually scared me
into making good records.

31:07.840 --> 31:09.220
You know? I mean, he had this, like...

31:09.320 --> 31:12.820
competitive spirit
that really blew my mind and...

31:12.920 --> 31:14.763
What about your mom?

31:16.840 --> 31:18.900
She stayed out of all of it, mostly.

31:19.000 --> 31:21.980
I think she drank a lot. You know?

31:22.080 --> 31:24.526
That's how she...
she... she dealt with it.

31:26.520 --> 31:30.820
I haven't seen her in... three years?

31:30.920 --> 31:33.260
- What?
- Gene doesn't think it's a good idea...

31:33.360 --> 31:35.328
for me to be in touch
with my family right now.

31:36.400 --> 31:39.060
I haven't seen my daughters in...

31:39.160 --> 31:40.810
two years.

31:43.040 --> 31:45.900
You have two daughters.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.129
Yeah. Yeah.

31:51.400 --> 31:53.260
I wasn't a very good father
to them, you know?

31:53.360 --> 31:56.940
Because I was drinking and drugging
when I should have been...

31:57.040 --> 31:58.780
you know, a parent.

31:58.880 --> 32:01.460
And, uh...

32:01.560 --> 32:03.660
you know, I made a mess of my life...

32:03.760 --> 32:05.900
lost control of my life.

32:06.000 --> 32:07.740
It's a weird trip...

32:07.840 --> 32:09.780
but...

32:09.880 --> 32:12.406
anyway, they live in Encino
with their mom.

32:16.200 --> 32:17.860
Well, shit.

32:17.960 --> 32:19.564
Yeah.

32:21.240 --> 32:23.660
But it's not so bad now anymore.

32:23.760 --> 32:25.220
You know?

32:25.320 --> 32:27.641
- Good.
- Uh-huh.

32:33.400 --> 32:34.526
Good.

32:34.640 --> 32:36.940
Look, listen to me,
I'm just going on and on.

32:37.040 --> 32:38.780
- It's my boring life...
- It's not boring.

32:38.880 --> 32:40.580
It is, but what about you, Melinda?

32:40.680 --> 32:43.660
I mean, my God, you're so...

32:43.760 --> 32:47.460
You're such good fun
and you're... you're so...

32:47.560 --> 32:49.820
so tender and so sweet.

32:49.920 --> 32:51.081
I mean...

32:52.360 --> 32:54.966
why don't you have a... boyfriend?

32:58.080 --> 33:00.686
Oh, well...

33:02.440 --> 33:04.124
There was someone.

33:05.960 --> 33:09.282
He was no good. He broke my heart.

33:11.760 --> 33:14.380
He shouldn't have done that.

33:14.480 --> 33:16.801
Well, I shouldn't have let him.

33:23.480 --> 33:25.660
Aww, sh...

33:25.760 --> 33:27.540
Fuck. Tony, you holding those keys down?

33:27.640 --> 33:28.740
- Yeah, yeah.
- Okay.

33:28.840 --> 33:31.320
Can I have another
bobby pin, please, Hal?

33:33.760 --> 33:35.540
Okay, keep the keys down, Tony.

33:35.640 --> 33:36.721
Here we go.

33:59.640 --> 34:01.180
Yeah, so, uh, right here.

34:01.280 --> 34:03.700
No, give it, uh...

34:03.800 --> 34:05.220
like...

34:05.320 --> 34:06.560
There's like a gasp in between.

34:13.800 --> 34:15.540
Cut! I think we got it.

34:15.639 --> 34:18.380
Chuck, mix that in, uh,
with the sound of the train...

34:18.480 --> 34:19.900
going by at the end of "Caroline, No."

34:20.000 --> 34:21.860
- You got it, Brian.
- Hey, Chuck...

34:21.960 --> 34:24.565
you think we could get a horse in here?

35:17.480 --> 35:19.005
Hey, kid.

35:20.480 --> 35:22.380
Brian.

35:22.480 --> 35:24.300
Brian!

35:24.400 --> 35:26.820
Brian! You got a light?

35:26.920 --> 35:29.571
I spilled coffee on my matches in there.

35:43.920 --> 35:45.380
Tough day at the office?

35:45.480 --> 35:47.820
Well...

35:47.920 --> 35:50.300
my family is coming in tomorrow...

35:50.400 --> 35:53.180
the band, they're...

35:53.280 --> 35:55.965
Well, sometimes they're tough, you know?

36:07.560 --> 36:09.244
Let me tell you something.

36:11.360 --> 36:13.860
We're all pros, you know?

36:13.960 --> 36:16.900
We've played with everyone.

36:17.000 --> 36:18.700
Heard it all.

36:18.800 --> 36:21.220
You name them, we've played with them.

36:21.320 --> 36:24.380
Sinatra, Dean Martin...

36:24.480 --> 36:27.460
Elvis, Phil Spector...

36:27.560 --> 36:31.380
Sam Cooke, everyone!

36:31.480 --> 36:34.404
And we all studied in goddamn
conservatories, for Christ's sake.

36:38.200 --> 36:40.380
But...

36:40.480 --> 36:43.180
but you...

36:43.280 --> 36:46.620
you got to know...

36:46.720 --> 36:48.245
that you're touched, kid.

36:50.680 --> 36:52.682
You've blown our minds.

36:57.120 --> 36:59.805
- More than Phil Spector?
- Ah, Phil's got nothing on you.

37:03.080 --> 37:04.820
Oh, man.

37:04.920 --> 37:07.500
No, the band is going to love it.

37:07.600 --> 37:09.250
Every note of it.

37:13.080 --> 37:14.844
You're a talented young man.

37:16.960 --> 37:19.167
Hang in there, man. I'll see ya.

37:25.080 --> 37:27.128
- I'll see ya tomorrow, Hal.

37:36.560 --> 37:38.740
- Wow, nice place.
- Yeah, come on in.

37:38.840 --> 37:40.171
Let me show you around.

37:45.400 --> 37:47.780
- Oh, wow.
- This is my room.

37:47.880 --> 37:49.325
This is my room.

37:51.320 --> 37:54.700
- Oh, nice!
- Yeah, I got to pick it.

37:54.800 --> 37:56.900
What do you mean?

37:57.000 --> 38:00.980
Well, you know, I got another house
a little bit up the coast, you know?

38:01.080 --> 38:03.020
- You do?
- But Gene wants me to live, you know...

38:03.120 --> 38:04.500
in a more controlled environment.

38:04.600 --> 38:07.140
So he's living in that one
and I'm living here.

38:07.240 --> 38:09.700
You know, not so many
distractions and memories.

38:09.800 --> 38:11.580
But I got to pick the room.

38:11.680 --> 38:13.125
- Wow.
- Ch... ch... check this out.

38:15.640 --> 38:17.244
Look at this.

38:56.560 --> 38:58.260
That's absolutely beautiful.

38:58.360 --> 38:59.860
Thanks.

38:59.960 --> 39:01.460
What is it?

39:01.560 --> 39:03.020
Oh, that's just something that I...

39:03.120 --> 39:04.963
came up with when I saw you.

39:07.240 --> 39:09.020
What are you going to do with it?

39:09.120 --> 39:11.340
Nothing, it's gone.

39:11.440 --> 39:13.044
That was just for you.

39:17.840 --> 39:19.620
That's so incredible. Oh, my God...

39:19.720 --> 39:21.660
that just, like, came out of you.

39:21.760 --> 39:23.900
Is that how it works? Or just...

39:24.000 --> 39:26.002
Yeah. Sometimes.

39:28.240 --> 39:31.780
Sometimes your inner voice
wants to express itself...

39:31.880 --> 39:33.740
and every once in a while,
every blue moon...

39:33.840 --> 39:36.220
your soul... comes out to play.

39:36.320 --> 39:37.700
- You know?
- Wow.

39:37.800 --> 39:39.700
Can't be rushed.

39:39.800 --> 39:41.700
It's like a kid, it's just nature...

39:41.800 --> 39:44.121
but... yeah.

39:48.640 --> 39:51.420
Can I ask you something personal?

39:51.520 --> 39:55.180
- Personal?
- Kind of.

39:55.280 --> 39:57.203
Sure, I'm an open book.

39:59.640 --> 40:02.450
Did you really spend two years in bed?

40:03.680 --> 40:05.540
No...

40:05.640 --> 40:07.290
more like three.

40:08.680 --> 40:10.409
At least, that's what I tell people.

40:14.360 --> 40:18.001
I got out at night
sometimes in my bathrobe.

40:22.080 --> 40:24.082
Do you like matzo ball soup?

40:25.880 --> 40:28.060
I don't know. I don't think...

40:28.160 --> 40:31.340
- I've ever had matzo ball soup.
- No?

40:31.440 --> 40:33.408
It's really good.

40:35.400 --> 40:37.540
My ex-wife was Jewish,
did I tell you that?

40:37.640 --> 40:39.180
- No.
- That's when I first had it.

40:39.280 --> 40:41.140
- Oh.
- At Marilyn's parents' house.

40:41.240 --> 40:42.890
They're really nice parents.

40:44.560 --> 40:46.540
She saved my life.

40:46.640 --> 40:48.580
Marilyn?

40:48.680 --> 40:49.820
Mare.

40:49.920 --> 40:52.380
I wasn't a very good husband,
I told you...

40:52.480 --> 40:54.420
but...

40:54.520 --> 40:56.568
we were only kids when we got married.

40:56.680 --> 40:59.809
- She was 16. 16.
- That's crazy.

41:02.280 --> 41:04.780
I think it's
an acquired taste, you know?

41:04.880 --> 41:08.123
- Marriage?
- Matzo ball soup.

41:09.880 --> 41:12.340
We should go one day, you know?

41:12.440 --> 41:13.780
- Go to Canter's and try it.
- Sure.

41:13.880 --> 41:16.180
- Do you want to try it?
- Yeah, I would. Why not?

41:16.280 --> 41:18.420
- I don't want to force you to.
- You wouldn't be.

41:18.520 --> 41:20.820
- It's not going to kill you or anything.
- I would hope not.

41:20.920 --> 41:22.540
You know, I mean,
just have a little bit.

41:22.640 --> 41:24.180
- It's good to try new things in life.
- Okay. I will.

41:24.280 --> 41:26.060
I will try to keep an open mind.

41:26.160 --> 41:28.180
- It's important to try things.
- Good.

41:28.280 --> 41:30.500
- New things.
- New things.

41:30.600 --> 41:31.522
I agree.

41:33.240 --> 41:35.180
Brian...

41:35.280 --> 41:36.850
time for your pills.

41:37.840 --> 41:39.330
Come on.

41:44.280 --> 41:47.329
- One minute.
- Oh.

41:49.800 --> 41:51.420
Melinda...

41:51.520 --> 41:53.700
you ever hear of the, um...

41:53.800 --> 41:56.300
"Underground Dictionary"?
Thank you, sweetheart.

41:56.400 --> 41:58.900
- Uh, no.
- Well, I published it.

41:59.000 --> 42:01.500
- 1971.
- Huh.

42:01.600 --> 42:03.220
It's an amazing book. It's a, uh...

42:03.320 --> 42:05.100
lexicon for subcultural speak.

42:05.200 --> 42:08.860
It's a reference book
for professionals...

42:08.960 --> 42:11.645
of all kinds to learn how to talk to...

42:13.200 --> 42:15.140
the subcultures of the time.

42:15.240 --> 42:18.940
- Bikers, hookers, surfers...
- Hey.

42:19.040 --> 42:20.580
- Are you okay?
- ...junkies, blacks...

42:20.680 --> 42:24.060
- Yeah.
- What does he have you on?

42:24.160 --> 42:27.500
I get allergies.
I get allergies, so, um...

42:27.600 --> 42:28.540
I get a little drowsy.

42:28.640 --> 42:30.290
They're the toughest ones to talk to.

42:30.400 --> 42:32.209
Right, Brian?

42:33.680 --> 42:36.260
I'm... I'm... I'm hungry, Gene.

42:36.360 --> 42:39.660
- ...It was a real bitchin' concept book.
- Gene, I'm hungry.

42:39.760 --> 42:41.900
Kind of ahead of its time
and it got a lot of attention.

42:42.000 --> 42:43.460
- Frankly.
- Gene, I'm hungry.

42:43.560 --> 42:45.100
It's coming.

42:45.200 --> 42:48.260
Uh, far out, right on, out of sight...

42:48.360 --> 42:50.442
uh, smokey tits, bonnaroo.

42:51.680 --> 42:54.900
Uh, super wicked, wiggy.

42:55.000 --> 42:58.100
How about that? All right.

42:58.200 --> 43:00.168
We got one ready here.

43:01.560 --> 43:03.340
Guest of honor first.

43:03.440 --> 43:04.580
- Oh.
- There you go, ma'am.

43:04.680 --> 43:07.300
- Nope.
- You know, I'm...

43:07.400 --> 43:09.620
- You... you should have it.
- No, no. He's not as hungry...

43:09.720 --> 43:11.529
- as he thinks he is.
- I'm... I'm hungry.

43:11.840 --> 43:13.580
No, you're not. You know what?

43:13.680 --> 43:15.460
You need to drink more water
and you would be full.

43:15.560 --> 43:18.166
- I think he's hungry.
- Go ahead. No, patience is a virtue.

43:18.280 --> 43:20.089
- Seriously, he can wait.
- I think he should...

43:20.200 --> 43:22.168
- I can share.
- Taste it.

43:30.240 --> 43:32.163
Good? Far out.

43:33.440 --> 43:34.771
Far out.

43:37.680 --> 43:38.980
- Hey, Gene.
- Yeah?

43:39.080 --> 43:41.700
Exactly what allergies
does he suffer from anyway?

43:41.800 --> 43:43.928
Don't you worry about that.

43:45.600 --> 43:48.540
Brian's medications
are very carefully administered...

43:48.640 --> 43:51.060
if you must know.

43:51.160 --> 43:54.340
You know what?
No, God damn it! Jesus Christ!

43:54.440 --> 43:56.660
Seriously?! Seriously?!

43:56.760 --> 44:00.460
You have got to learn
to wait your goddamn turn!

44:00.560 --> 44:03.180
Jesus Christ!

44:03.280 --> 44:05.220
Now this is what happens, okay?

44:05.320 --> 44:06.820
- I'm hungry.
- No!

44:06.920 --> 44:10.220
You are not goddamn hungry!
You think you're hungry!

44:10.320 --> 44:13.180
Do you you understand
the goddamn difference?!

44:13.280 --> 44:15.500
Wait your turn!

44:15.600 --> 44:17.602
You have got to be kidding me!

44:20.240 --> 44:23.140
You have no idea
the consequences from this.

44:23.240 --> 44:25.020
- Okay?
- No.

44:25.120 --> 44:28.488
No idea, man! Come on!

44:28.600 --> 44:30.807
Jesus Christ! Rob?

44:48.320 --> 44:51.500
First of all, I want to apologize
about the other night.

44:51.600 --> 44:55.260
I can get worked up
sometimes when it comes to Brian.

44:55.360 --> 44:57.580
Now, I should have
met with you earlier...

44:57.680 --> 45:00.220
but with all of that said...

45:00.320 --> 45:02.180
I really don't want you to be alarmed...

45:02.280 --> 45:05.460
by what, uh, I'm going
to talk to you about now.

45:05.560 --> 45:08.660
But you should know
that you are dealing with...

45:08.760 --> 45:12.300
a very, very... sick man.

45:12.400 --> 45:14.420
There's no other way to say it. Sorry.

45:14.520 --> 45:16.860
Well, how sick is he?

45:16.960 --> 45:20.203
Brian is a... paranoid schizophrenic.

45:21.400 --> 45:23.900
But you really
do not need to be alarmed...

45:24.000 --> 45:25.420
because I have it under control.

45:25.520 --> 45:28.380
I am the control... so to speak.

45:28.480 --> 45:30.340
When I started working with Brian...

45:30.440 --> 45:33.220
he weighed, what... 300 pounds?

45:33.320 --> 45:35.580
He spent all day in bed...

45:35.680 --> 45:38.540
eating bloody steaks
and a lot of junk food.

45:38.640 --> 45:41.140
- Self-medicating.
- Oh.

45:41.240 --> 45:43.940
Drinking, among other things.

45:44.040 --> 45:47.660
Uh, just not dealing,
not able to look me in the eye.

45:47.760 --> 45:50.620
Not able to look anybody in the eye.

45:50.720 --> 45:52.180
Frankly, suicidal.

45:52.280 --> 45:54.260
- So...
- Really?

45:54.360 --> 45:56.620
I pulled him out of the grave...

45:56.720 --> 45:58.940
and I stood him up...

45:59.040 --> 46:02.089
and I taught him
how to start living again.

46:04.040 --> 46:07.940
He was very open,
I mean, he... I... thought.

46:08.040 --> 46:09.100
You know, he told me...

46:09.200 --> 46:10.964
he was taking medication for anxiety...

46:11.080 --> 46:13.700
- and a little depression.
- First thing, don't...

46:13.800 --> 46:15.980
believe everything that Brian tells you.

46:16.080 --> 46:19.700
He's, uh...- he's a little boy
in a man's body.

46:19.800 --> 46:21.723
I mean, there's a lot
of playacting going on...

46:21.840 --> 46:23.922
in Brian World.
Are you in love with him?

46:28.240 --> 46:31.420
Please understand something.
I hope you do.

46:31.520 --> 46:33.740
It's my job... it's my duty...

46:33.840 --> 46:36.940
to approve anyone that
Brian is spending time with.

46:37.040 --> 46:39.042
And I mean everyone.

46:40.520 --> 46:42.249
Yeah? So...

46:42.360 --> 46:43.940
If you want to continue to see him...

46:44.040 --> 46:46.420
well, then there's
going to have to be some rules.

46:46.520 --> 46:48.180
Um, for example...

46:48.280 --> 46:50.780
if Brian calls you,
asks you out for a date...

46:50.880 --> 46:52.140
well, that's fantastic...

46:52.240 --> 46:55.528
but I need you to call me
directly... immediately.

46:56.920 --> 46:58.460
And afterwards, I think it would be...

46:58.560 --> 47:00.180
therapeutically useful...

47:00.280 --> 47:03.180
if you report to me
everything that happened.

47:03.280 --> 47:05.180
Your thoughts, your feelings.

47:05.280 --> 47:06.940
Uh, his thoughts, his feelings.

47:07.040 --> 47:09.500
And so far as you can report
on those things objectively...

47:09.600 --> 47:12.220
from your perspective. You follow me?

47:12.320 --> 47:15.340
I'm giving you
unprecedented access here.

47:15.440 --> 47:19.180
But... I need you...

47:19.280 --> 47:21.500
to work with me.

47:21.600 --> 47:23.540
All right, you want a cup of tea?

47:23.640 --> 47:25.620
But, you know, your suspicion...

47:25.720 --> 47:27.980
is just like Brian's initial paranoia.

47:28.080 --> 47:30.300
His desire not to get better.

47:30.400 --> 47:31.820
But, you know, that came from...

47:31.920 --> 47:33.540
no sense of self-worth...

47:33.640 --> 47:37.060
no belief in himself,
no ability to trust.

47:37.160 --> 47:39.700
You have the ability to trust, Melinda?

47:39.800 --> 47:41.060
Come on.

47:41.160 --> 47:44.300
I'm helping a great man
learn how to be alive again.

47:44.400 --> 47:46.402
Why not trust me?

47:47.800 --> 47:49.740
I'm going to try, Gene.
I just don't know you.

47:49.840 --> 47:51.922
But I know you.

47:53.200 --> 47:56.010
As I told you, it is my job.

47:57.120 --> 47:59.260
Okay?

47:59.360 --> 48:02.060
You think of yourself
as an independent woman, right?

48:02.160 --> 48:04.420
Hagerty girl, right?

48:04.520 --> 48:06.460
Successful modeling career...

48:06.560 --> 48:08.900
some long-term relationships...

48:09.000 --> 48:11.020
disappointments.

48:11.120 --> 48:13.540
Your last boyfriend
took you for a bit of a ride.

48:13.640 --> 48:16.689
Had a girl in every port.

48:17.840 --> 48:19.580
And now you...

48:19.680 --> 48:21.250
sell cars.

48:22.200 --> 48:23.850
Well, we all do what we can.

48:23.960 --> 48:25.420
We do.

48:25.520 --> 48:27.140
And life can be painful.

48:27.240 --> 48:30.130
I know. That's all I'm saying.

48:32.880 --> 48:35.100
You know, I don't believe
in coincidences.

48:35.200 --> 48:37.123
There's a reason we met.

48:38.240 --> 48:41.767
All of us. Let's work together.

48:43.320 --> 48:46.740
Help me out and let me help you...

48:46.840 --> 48:49.525
and help me help Brian. Okay?

48:50.640 --> 48:52.580
Thanks, Gene. Thank you.

48:52.680 --> 48:54.489
Take good care of yourself.

50:02.800 --> 50:04.740
Konnichiwa.

50:04.840 --> 50:06.780
- Where's my favorite big brother?
- Denny!

50:06.880 --> 50:08.980
How you doing? Oh, hey.

50:09.080 --> 50:11.500
Hey, man, forget about California girls.

50:11.600 --> 50:14.660
- Tokyo is where it's at!
- Tokyo girls? Denny.

50:14.760 --> 50:17.081
- I missed you, Bri.
- Oh, it's good to see you.

50:17.200 --> 50:18.860
Hey, look, I got you a souvenir.

50:18.960 --> 50:20.700
Hey, it matches your shirt. It's cool.

50:20.800 --> 50:22.620
- Hey, Al, good to see you!
- Good to see you.

50:22.720 --> 50:25.380
- Bruce, thanks for being there for me.
- It's an honor, Brian.

50:25.480 --> 50:27.740
No way to fill your shoes,
but I did my best.

50:27.840 --> 50:28.980
- Cousin.
- Mike!

50:29.080 --> 50:30.764
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you!

50:30.880 --> 50:32.900
- What happened? Look at that beard!
- I know, I know...

50:33.000 --> 50:35.220
but what happened to you?
You're getting a little tubby here.

50:35.320 --> 50:37.020
What happened?
You should go on a fast with me.

50:37.120 --> 50:38.860
Well, I'm already eating
as fast as I can.

50:38.960 --> 50:41.780
Well, fatty, we are ready
to rock to your roll, man.

50:41.880 --> 50:43.820
- Let's... let's listen to some tracks.
- Good to see you.

50:43.920 --> 50:45.251
- All right!
- What you got cooking?

50:45.360 --> 50:48.060
You know, Carl, a samurai sword
would have been...

50:48.160 --> 50:49.500
Well, yeah, but I just...

50:49.600 --> 50:51.284
- it was in the airport.
- Does it look cool?

50:51.400 --> 50:55.420
I try hard to be strong...

50:55.520 --> 51:00.740
but sometimes I fail myself...

51:00.840 --> 51:04.580
And after all I've promised you...

51:04.680 --> 51:07.220
so faithfully...

51:07.320 --> 51:09.380
you still...

51:09.480 --> 51:11.940
believe...

51:12.040 --> 51:15.761
in me.

51:17.360 --> 51:22.048
I want to cry...

51:50.720 --> 51:53.460
Hey, Brian? This chorus.

51:53.560 --> 51:56.300
The lyrics.

51:56.400 --> 51:58.780
Don't you think it's a little, uh...

51:58.880 --> 52:00.980
What?

52:01.080 --> 52:03.321
"Hang on to your ego,"
what are you trying to say?

52:04.520 --> 52:06.300
Uh...

52:06.400 --> 52:07.820
well...

52:07.920 --> 52:09.500
- "hang on to your ego."
- Yeah, ego.

52:09.600 --> 52:11.860
Are you saying...

52:11.960 --> 52:13.820
Is this a druggie song?
Is this a drug song?

52:13.920 --> 52:17.140
- A drug song?
- Yes, "hang on to your ego."

52:17.240 --> 52:20.164
Uh, "Hang on, but I know
that you're going to lose the fight."

52:20.280 --> 52:23.660
I don't know. I... I don't think
it's a drug song...

52:23.760 --> 52:25.860
- whatever that is.
- "They come on like they're peaceful...

52:25.960 --> 52:27.660
but inside they're so uptight.

52:27.760 --> 52:31.500
They trip through the day
and waste all their thoughts at night."

52:31.600 --> 52:33.180
Sounds like a druggie to me, Brian.

52:33.280 --> 52:35.500
- Druggie?!
- Don't pretend like you don't know...

52:35.600 --> 52:39.400
- what I'm talking about here!
- Okay, it's about ego. That's all.

52:42.040 --> 52:43.565
It's about ego?

52:43.680 --> 52:46.729
That's all? Okay.

52:48.280 --> 52:50.940
I'm not trying to be
a tough guy here, okay?

52:51.040 --> 52:53.580
I'm just asking a question.
I just want to know if it's a drug song.

52:53.680 --> 52:55.020
If it's not a drug song,
I want to know what it's about.

52:55.120 --> 52:56.540
Does it sound like
a drug song to anybody else?

52:56.640 --> 52:58.020
Okay, it's not a drug song,
but is it about...

52:58.120 --> 52:59.500
I don't know, it sounds fine.

52:59.600 --> 53:01.460
Okay, okay, so hang on...
we'll hang on to our ego.

53:01.560 --> 53:03.700
Let's all just hang on to our egos
and record the song.

53:03.800 --> 53:05.940
She made me feel so bad.

53:06.040 --> 53:08.008
She made my heart feel sad.

53:08.120 --> 53:10.100
She made my days go wrong.

53:10.200 --> 53:12.060
And then my nights so long.

53:12.160 --> 53:14.060
You've got to keep in mind...

53:14.160 --> 53:17.260
love is here...

53:17.360 --> 53:21.020
today, and it's gone...

53:21.120 --> 53:26.843
tomorrow. It's here and gone so fast.

53:36.600 --> 53:39.020
You have that attached to the flash?

53:39.120 --> 53:41.885
Brian, your voice is on the track.

53:43.480 --> 53:45.020
Stop, please.

53:45.120 --> 53:46.740
Yeah!

53:46.840 --> 53:48.126
No.

53:49.680 --> 53:51.682
- Yes.
- What do you mean, "yeah"?

53:54.760 --> 53:57.020
I mean, yeah, I left them in.

53:57.120 --> 53:58.460
I like it.

53:58.560 --> 54:00.380
- We're listening here.
- You left them in?

54:00.480 --> 54:02.100
The voices? The talking in your head?

54:02.200 --> 54:04.060
That's part of the song?

54:04.160 --> 54:06.980
- It's part of the music.
- Keep in mind love is here.

54:07.080 --> 54:09.940
It's just like all
the other instruments we use.

54:10.040 --> 54:12.780
- Play the studio.
- Today, and it's gone...

54:12.880 --> 54:15.540
- Play the studio?
- ...tomorrow, it's here...

54:15.640 --> 54:17.620
- Play the studio?
- I like it, Bri.

54:17.720 --> 54:19.380
They're not going to hear it anyways.

54:19.480 --> 54:21.420
It's buried under there.
I... I think it's really cool.

54:21.520 --> 54:24.060
- Can we stop it, please?
- Jesus, come on, Mike.

54:24.160 --> 54:26.300
No, no, no, it's amateurish.
It's amateurish.

54:26.400 --> 54:28.260
It's hip, man! It's fun!

54:28.360 --> 54:30.340
It's now!
That's where things are happening.

54:30.440 --> 54:31.780
- Brian, it's not.
- Now!

54:31.880 --> 54:33.220
No, this is not fun.

54:33.320 --> 54:35.180
- Not the music, not the lyrics.
- I think it's fun.

54:35.280 --> 54:36.980
Now, it's not all bad,
don't get me wrong...

54:37.080 --> 54:38.980
but it's not Beach Boys fun.

54:39.080 --> 54:41.460
- We've done Beach Boys fun.
- And we had hits, we had lots of hits!

54:41.560 --> 54:43.180
- Why are we arguing right now, Mike?
- There's not one hit...

54:43.280 --> 54:44.540
on this album, guys!

54:44.640 --> 54:46.860
I don't care how many car horns
and bicycle bells...

54:46.960 --> 54:48.780
and jingle-jangle
or whatever you put in there.

54:48.880 --> 54:51.300
They're not going to buy
something depressing like that!

54:51.400 --> 54:54.140
- Depressing?
- Even the happy songs are sad.

54:54.240 --> 54:56.460
We need to write
some of the old stuff again, fellas.

54:56.560 --> 54:58.324
- That's all I'm saying.
- The old stuff is old!

54:58.440 --> 55:01.100
- So we'll make it new again!
- I can't go back in time!

55:01.200 --> 55:02.660
We're not surfers, we never have been...

55:02.760 --> 55:04.660
and real surfers
don't dig our music anyway.

55:04.760 --> 55:07.127
- They don't.
- Okay, I can't write about the summer...

55:07.240 --> 55:10.340
and fun and summer
and summer and fun and cars!

55:10.440 --> 55:12.460
I got different stuff inside me.

55:12.560 --> 55:13.860
I got to get it out.

55:13.960 --> 55:15.340
Oh, jeez, would you listen to yourself?

55:15.440 --> 55:17.660
You've "got to get it out"?

55:17.760 --> 55:19.842
- Who are you? Mozart?!
- Everyone shut up!

55:19.960 --> 55:21.860
Carl, play it again.

55:21.960 --> 55:23.980
It's a new creative bag.

55:24.080 --> 55:27.820
- We've got to keep growing!
- Oh, jeez.

55:27.920 --> 55:30.740
None of these guys have played
one single note on the entire album.

55:30.840 --> 55:33.420
It's like you're making
your own record with our voices, Brian.

55:33.520 --> 55:35.260
Dennis played.

55:35.360 --> 55:36.940
- A little bit. Carl, too.
- "A little bit."

55:37.040 --> 55:39.088
For crying out loud,
would you listen to yourself?

55:40.080 --> 55:41.620
First you wanted
to stop touring with us...

55:41.720 --> 55:43.620
and we accepted that, that's fine.
Bruce is doing great.

55:43.720 --> 55:45.500
But now it's like we're barely a part...

55:45.600 --> 55:47.489
of the Brian Wilson Band!

55:49.120 --> 55:51.441
You can't just do
whatever the hell you want, Brian!

55:57.120 --> 55:59.327
The other guys might not say this...

56:01.080 --> 56:02.684
but you are letting us down.

56:05.520 --> 56:07.740
If you stop thinking about
yourself for two seconds...

56:07.840 --> 56:09.490
you might realize that.

56:30.920 --> 56:33.260
Break my heart.

56:33.360 --> 56:37.540
I want to go and cry.

56:37.640 --> 56:40.220
It's so sad...

56:40.320 --> 56:44.220
to watch a sweet thing die.

56:44.320 --> 56:49.380
Oh, Caroline, why?

56:49.480 --> 56:56.100
Could I ever find in you again...

56:56.200 --> 57:02.700
the things that made me
love you so much then?

57:02.800 --> 57:06.580
Could we ever bring them back...

57:06.680 --> 57:11.083
once they have gone?

57:14.680 --> 57:19.720
Oh, Caroline, no.

57:22.720 --> 57:24.940
Sorry, sorry, Brian,
but apparently your dad...

57:25.040 --> 57:26.700
just drove up.
I thought you'd want to know.

57:26.800 --> 57:29.167
- Shit!
- Hide the pot!

57:31.400 --> 57:32.845
Fuck!

57:41.760 --> 57:43.820
- Uncle Murray!
- Boys?

57:43.920 --> 57:45.900
- Hey, hey, hey.
- Mike, Al.

